    section
        h2 About Comfort, Texas
        .content
          .text
            p A Hill Country gem operating at a different speed. Founded by German freethinkers in the 1850s, Comfort remains an independent, unincorporated community to this day. The town draws treasure hunters, entrepreneurs, and a unique mix of residents seeking a slower pace in Texas's famed Hill Country. River floats, wine-tasting, antiques, and wildlife all within reach. We're excited to share this treasured town with y'all! Here are a few of our favorite spots:
            h3 In town
            p.noPad #[a(href='https://the8thstreetmarket.com' target='_blank') The 8th Street Market] - Enjoy a cup of local Merit coffee while you browse carefully curated antiques and architectural salvage. 
            p #[a(href='https://www.highscafeandstore.com/#comfort-food-for-you' target='_blank') High's Cafe] - Fresh lunch fare, a favorite of the Mother of the Groom!
            p #[a(href='https://www.wanderncalf.com' target='_blank') Wander'n Calf] - House-roasted coffee & scratch bakery.
            p #[a(href='https://www.facebook.com/The-Comfort-Meet-Market-210762872315803' target='_blank') Meet Market] - Local watering hole with an impressive amount of Beatles memorabilia.
            h3 Further out
            p.noPad #[a(href='https://southoldfarmandcellar.com' target='_blank') Southold Wine + Cellar] - #[i Fredericksburg] - A favorite destination for natural wines, local snacks, and panoramic vistas.
            p #[a(href='https://wineforthepeople.com/' target='_blank') Wine for the People] and #[a(href='https://www.instagram.com/brucieatx/?hl=en' target='_blank') Brucie] - #[i Austin] - Excellent tasting room for local wines, and home of new food truck favorite Brucie!
            p #[i Johnson City, Fredericksburg, Boerne,] and #[i Kerrville] - other lovely Hill Country towns worth exploring!
